---

<Layout>
  <head slot="head">
    <title>Community — Wedding Photo Hangover</title>
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://weddinghangover.com/community/" />
    <meta name="description" content="Join the Wedding Photo Hangover community on Facebook and beyond." />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Wedding Photo Hangover - A Wedding Photography Podcast" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Community — Wedding Photo Hangover" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Join the Wedding Photo Hangover community on Facebook and beyond." />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://weddinghangover.com/community" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="/images/global/WPH_Wide_CleanNB.webp" />
    <meta property="og:image:width" content="1500" />
    <meta property="og:image:height" content="843" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Community — Wedding Photo Hangover" />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Join the Wedding Photo Hangover community on Facebook and beyond." />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="/images/global/WPH_Wide_CleanNB.webp" />
    <meta name="twitter:url" content="https://weddinghangover.com/community" />
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Community — Wedding Photo Hangover" />
    <meta itemprop="description" content="Join the Wedding Photo Hangover community on Facebook and beyond." />
    <meta itemprop="url" content="https://weddinghangover.com/community" />
    <meta itemprop="image" content="/images/global/WPH_Wide_CleanNB.webp" />
  </head>

  <main>
    <Hero 
      title="Join Our Amazing Listener Community" 
      background="/images/index/wph-community.webp" 
    />

    <div class="content-container">
      <section>
        <h2>Community</h2>
        <p>
          We don’t like to brag, but we have the best listeners. If you want to get involved in the awesome community of listeners supporting the best photography podcast, then you can always see what people are instagramming, tweeting, and facebooking. 
          <br /><br />
          If you really want to get involved though and have the opportunity to submit questions for special guests and see topics we’re planning to discuss on the podcast ahead of time, then you have to join the 
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/2143595509211422" target="_blank">Wedding Hangover Facebook Group</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/2143595509211422" target="_blank">
          <img src="/images/community/wph-community-hero.webp" alt="Wedding Hangover Facebook Group" style="max-width:100%; height:auto;" />
        </a>
      </section>

      <section>
        <blockquote style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.5rem; font-style: italic; color: #666;">
          “Best Podcast Ever!!<br />
          I heard them as guests on another podcast and started listening immediately. They hijacked ALL of my free time because I couldn’t stop binging, and I am just now finally finishing up the last one. My only regret is that there weren’t a few more years worth of shows in the archives.”
        </blockquote>
        <p style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0.5rem;">— David Ferry, Facebook Review</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
